## Mandatory Pre-Implementation Checks

### Before Any Color Change
```typescript
// Required validation function
const validateContrast = (foreground: string, background: string): boolean => {
  const ratio = calculateContrastRatio(foreground, background);
  return ratio >= 4.5; // WCAG AA minimum
};

// Usage example
if (!validateContrast('#8B5C9E', '#ffffff')) {
  throw new Error('Contrast ratio too low for accessibility');
}
```

### Text Hierarchy Validation
- [ ] **H1**: Navy (#1e3a5f) on light backgrounds only
- [ ] **H2**: Purple (#8B5C9E) on white backgrounds only  
- [ ] **H3**: Navy with 80% opacity minimum
- [ ] **Body Text**: #2a2a2a or darker for maximum readability
- [ ] **Captions**: #666666 minimum (7.1:1 on white)
- [ ] **Links**: Purple (#8B5C9E) with underline, Navy hover

## Screen Reader Compatibility

### Color-Independent Information
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Information not dependent on color alone
<div className="bg-red-100 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-4">
  <div className="flex">
    <ExclamationTriangleIcon className="h-5 w-5 text-red-400" />
    <div className="ml-3">
      <p className="text-sm text-red-700">
        <span className="sr-only">Error: </span>
        Please fill in all required fields.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

// ❌ INCORRECT - Relies on color alone
<p className="text-red-500">Required field</p>
```

### ARIA Labels and Descriptions
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Descriptive labels
<button 
  className="bg-soi-navy text-white"
  aria-label="Book appointment with orthopedic specialist"
  aria-describedby="booking-help"
>
  Book Now
</button>
<div id="booking-help" className="sr-only">
  Opens booking form in new window
</div>
```

